def: A chart of a course, esp. at sea. [Obs.]
A body of followers; -- applied to the lawless or brigand bandsin Italy and Sicily.
Having some of the forms, such as drapery or the like, toosharply defined. "An edgy style of sculpture." Hazlitt.
A combining form used in anatomy to indicate connection with,or relation to, the tibia; as, tibiotarsus, tibiofibular.
Crystallography of organic forms; -- a division of morphologycreated by Haeckel. It is essentially stereometric, and relates to amathematical conception of organic forms. See Tectology.
One who performs, accomplishes, or fulfills; as, a goodpromiser, but a bad performer; especially, one who shows skill andtraining in any art; as, a performer of the drama; a performer on theharp.
